# Web Testing Conventions

- Use `Vitest` for unit and component tests in `apps/web`.
- Colocate `Vitest` test files with the code they cover, using `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`.
- Keep shared test infrastructure in `apps/web/src/test/`.
- Keep shared network mocking in `apps/web/src/test/msw/`.
- Add shared fixtures or reusable test helpers under `apps/web/src/test/` only when multiple areas need them.
- Keep feature-specific test data or helpers close to the feature instead of centralizing everything too early.
- Future `Playwright` tests should live in a separate browser test area such as `apps/web/tests/e2e/`, not next to components.
- Prefer behavior-focused tests with `React Testing Library`; avoid low-value snapshot-heavy tests for mostly presentational UI.
- Cover rule-heavy logic with focused tests in the same implementation phase.
- After meaningful test-related or rule-related changes in `apps/web`, run `bun run test:run`.

Example:

```text
src/components/cart/CartDrawer.tsx
src/components/cart/CartDrawer.test.tsx
src/lib/cart/merge-cart-lines.ts
src/lib/cart/merge-cart-lines.test.ts
src/test/msw/server.ts
tests/e2e/cart-smoke.spec.ts
```
